The article discusses a message from the President of the United States, Barack Obama, regarding the continuation of the national emergency with respect to persons who commit, threaten to commit, or support terrorism. According to Section 202(d) of the National Emergencies Act, a national emergency automatically terminates unless the President publishes a notice stating that it is to continue in effect. The President states that the crisis caused by acts of terrorism, including the September 11, 2001 attacks, has not been resolved and poses an ongoing threat to national security, foreign policy, and the economy. Therefore, he has determined that it is necessary to continue the national emergency and maintain comprehensive sanctions to address this threat. The message was sent on September 11, 2012.